{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place flat-leaf parsley in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place water in mixing bowl. Scrub and de-beard mussels, if necessary, and place in Varoma dish, set Varoma in position and steam <b>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma and check that mussels have all opened. If not, remove open mussels and transfer to a bowl, set Varoma back in position and steam a further <b>5-10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma, discard any mussels that remain closed, transfer open mussels to bowl and set aside. Strain the cooking liquid through a fine mesh strainer into another bowl and set aside.","Place extra virgin olive oil, shallots, garlic cloves and red chilli in mixing bowl and chop <b>7 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl using spatula.","Sauté <b>3 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add white wine and cherry tomatoes and cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add tomato purée and reserved cooking liquid, adding water to reach 700 g, then bring to a boil <b>7 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add salt and penne and cook for <b>time indicated on packet\/100°C\/\/speed <b> or until al dente. Meanwhile, remove mussels from opened shells, reserving some mussels in their shells for garnish, and set aside.","Transfer pasta to a serving bowl, add reserved steamed mussels, combine using spatula and drizzle with extra virgin olive oil. Garnish with reserved chopped parsley and reserved mussels in their shells. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 - 5 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only,","250 g water, plus extra as needed","1000 g fresh mussels, shells scrubbed and de-bearded","30 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for serving","30 g shallots, cut in halves","3 garlic cloves","1 fresh red chilli, small, deseeded (optional)","50 g dry white wine              (optional)","120 g cherry tomatoes, cut in halves","40 - 50 g tomato purée (concentrated)","1 pinch salt","350 g penne or similar short dried pasta"]}],"id":"r80492","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-rmNlX5MGE3I\/XZMyuDsIlHI\/AAAAAAAAaoo\/qBrLVnRLSXo5tHFR4XtqOJfCJpnAAESbwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_LGqJN5FDKGTAhpGf.png","title":"Penne with mussels","publishedAt":"2017-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17 g","fat":"15 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"65 g","calories":"2011 kJ \/ 480 kcal"},"usefulItems":"fine-mesh strainer","hintsAndTricks":["In this dish the cooking method is borrowed from risotto: the pasta absorbs the liquid released by the mussels and at the same time adds starch to the sauce for a creamy and mouth-watering result. Add a little kick of chilli if you wish.","Fresh mussels can be replaced with frozen mussels. In this case, they must be defrosted first."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","1h 5m","4 portions"]}